item.title: I get a lot of comments saying, "OF models just make content for attention", so he's some perspective..
item.description: https://www.instagram.com/totallynotsibby We all know the system is fucked, but then we blame people getting fucked by the system for surviving in ways that doesn't hurt anyone else. Attention is not the end goal, survival is. Someone will say, it's still for attention, but then what the fuck isn't? Most goods and services you use advertise, all you're pointing out is that OF models often run every aspect of the business themselves. But why not going around pointing out that Star Wars just makes movies for the attention? Because it's just a dumb thing to complain about. Your comment saying, "it's just for attention", is just as much for attention as their content.

item.title: Minneapolis beat ICE!!!
item.description: Second edit: Ok so it seems we have landed somewhere in the middle. Politico has the scoop on the exit from Minneapolis, key points: -Bovino is leaving for sure -Discharge and Gov Walz had a call and have an agreement on the withdrawal from Minnesota. -The number of departures in unknown -Homan is stepping in for Bovino or damage control, unclear -Noem’s leadership and the overall handling of the crisis is being questioned by republicans Source: https://www.politico.com/news/2026/01/26/white-house-reckons-with-gop-backlash-after-federal-agents-kill-a-second-person-in-minneapolis-00746737 Edit: I may have jumped the gun on the news, that’s on me. The original post that broke the news has been deleted and we’re waiting for a better source to confirm the scale of retreat. Here’s the source talking about the deleted posts https://bsky.app/profile/atrupar.com/post/3mde5u3oqls2l Original post: https://bsky.app/profile/iwriteok.bsky.social/post/3mde5fxcu3c2z Doesn’t matter where they go next, Minneapolis taught us how to beat them.
